Introduction¶

I will analys Movies data set tmdb-movies.csv

This data set contains information about 10,000 movies collected from The Movie Database (TMDb), including user ratings and revenue. ● Certain columns, like ‘cast’ and ‘genres’, contain multiple values separated by pipe (|)characters.
Goal:\ analyzing this amazing dataset and find intersting factes What makes a profitable movie?\ get some interesting statistical insights\ Answer some questions like The most commonly produced genres? \ What month has the most content added?\ Most Movie Runtime ? , Explore Movies characteristics before and after 2000?

Starting By wrangle and clean the dataset. then visualize the findings.

websites I used¶

https://www.kaggle.com/ , https://seaborn.pydata.org/ , https://stackoverflow.com/ ,https://pandas.pydata.org/

from collections import Counter
def convert_column (column):
    list1 = list()
    for item in column:
        item =(item.replace('|',','))
        list1.append(item.split(','))
    one_d =list()
    for item in list1:
        for item1 in item:
            one_d.append(item1)

        x= Counter(one_d)
        x ={k: v for k, v in sorted(x.items(), key=lambda item: item[1] ,reverse=True)}
       
        
    
    return x
